  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Thou hast also given me the necks of mine enemies,.... Either to slay them, or to trample or put a yoke upon them; or rather the sense is, thou hast made them to fly before me, to turn their necks or backs unto me, as the word is used in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 7:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; and it is expressive of an utter rout and vanquishing of them; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that I might destroy them that hate me; they not being able to face him and stand against him. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "that I might destroy them that hate me; they not being able to face him and stand against him. ",
            "children": []
          },
